/*
:name: cast_overflow_const
:type: error
:error: does not fit the .* cast range
*/

// A sized cast `uN`/`sN` is CHECKED, not truncating (07-typesystem). A
// compile-time constant that overflows the target is a compile error — use a
// `wrap`/`sat` prefix to drop bits intentionally (`wrap val = 0x1F0`).
mut val:u8 = 0
val = u8(0x1F0)
